On 2-Jul-04, at 10:51 AM, Bob Forrester wrote:

> I have the same problem.  Brand new VDO CHT gage just installed on my 
> bus.  Used only the provided materials for the install (i.e., no extra 
> wire length needed). Found that the wires in the harness were swapped 
> such that the black wire needs to connect to the + terminal and the 
> red to the - terminal.  On a short 10 minute drive to work at 35 mph, 
> I'm getting 360 degree readings.  This on a newly rebuilt engine with 
> a newly rebuilt and adjusted AFM.  Driving down the freeway yesterday 
> at 60-65 MPH I was getting 400-425 degree readings. Oil temps the 
> whole time were about 180 degrees.
